title: [branch-2.0](migrate disk) fix migrate disk lost data during publish version #29887
body:
pick: #29887

Tablet migrate disk may cause lost data. For example, suppose the old tablet's version is 10, it's just publish txn on version 11. At then comes a migrate disk task. After the old tablet just finish publish txn 11, but before it add rowset( version = 11). For the migrating task, the old tablet had no txn now, so the new tablet will copy the old tablet's data(old tablet's version is still 10). After copying, it will delete the old tablet, and replace it with the new tablet.
So data whose version is 11 will be lost.

title: [enhancement](stmt-forward) record query result for proxy query to avoid EOF
body:
## Proposed changes

Originally, if the forwarded statement is a query statement, the query result will be sent to the Master MySQL channel directly, rather than replied to Follower. But actually, these packets should be sent to the Follower MySQL channel.

Therefore, we should record these packets and response them to Follower, so that they could be written to the right channel to avoid weird EOF result when forwarding a query statement.

Most of queries won't be forwarded to master, however, this case does be triggered if follower is far behind master or it is transfering to master..., anyway, making this case assignable.

## Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

**Description**

The UTF8 format of the Windows system has BOM. 

We add a new user property to `Outfile/Export`Therefore, when exporting Doris data, users can choose whether to bring BOM on the beginning of the CSV file.

**Usage:**
```sql
-- outfile:
select * from demo.student
into outfile "file:///xxx/export/exp_"
format as csv
properties(
    "column_separator" = ",",
    "with_bom" = "true"
);

-- Export:
EXPORT TABLE student TO "file:///xx/tmpdata/export/exp_"
PROPERTIES(
    "format" = "csv",

);
```
